	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Okay I stated we were going to try Bazzt again the next day I think... Well we failed. We did, although, clear plane of sky around 40 days later on our next raid.<BR>
<BR>
Here's the scoop on GSoT.<BR>
<BR>
Drops needed:<BR>
<BR>
Aged Nectar: randomly off bees on 6<BR>
Writ of Quellious: randomly off drakes on 7<BR>
Glowing Diamond (no drop version): eye of veeshan<BR>
<BR>
We killed the eye twice, but it seems to randomly drop the rare for the last sky quest for each class... which means your class has a 1 in 14 chance of completing this quest each time the eye is killed.<BR>
<BR>
On a side note on sky quests... I've seen a lot of people bicker over drops and not getting their quest items.<BR>
<BR>
All that matters for finishing ANY quest in the plane of sky are the rare drops. each quest has 3 or 4 items needed and almost all quests have 1 rare drop and in a couple cases 2. If you're lucky enough to win a rare, you can get the commons easy enough.<BR>
<BR>
Heck, we have 1 monk with the aged nectar now and 2 other monks in the guild with the writ in our guild. I'm sure if one of us wins a glowing diamond our next trip to sky, we'd work out something so they could complete the quest on the spot.<BR>
<BR>
Only two guilds on our server have cleared sky though, and we were the first... not many people are going to get a chance at this quest item, and there's better haste items out there now (41% haste sandals in VP) anyway. My point being though, that unless you work cooperatively, and are willing to sacrifice for the sake of others, often times, you won't succeed as a whole.<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
