				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Are you sure you have this one? For one thing, some items in sky were changed to reflect the risk/reward factor.<BR>
<BR>
Also the quest monk haste item &quot;Golden Sash of Tranquility&quot; is a LOT tougher to get than the monk haste belt which randomly drops off certain mabs called &quot;Belt of Tranquility&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
The quest SASH gives 41% haste as tested by a monk ON A LIVE SERVER who has finished the quest.<BR>
<BR>
I'm actually strolling these boards now to find out which quest items are needed to finish this and who drops them - found out the items needed are:<BR>
<BR>
*Aged Necter - drops off Bazzt Zzzt (boss of island 6)<BR>
*Writ of Quellious - haven't found info yet<BR>
*Glowing Diamond - haven't found info yet<BR>
<BR>
I've been told that the necter only drops off the island 6 boss who has a nasty disease based Area Effect DoT which spans the whole island when cast. He also hits for up to 850 damage PER HIT. I know this because earlier tonight we fought him - we lost but had him down to close to 1 or 2% life tops... going at him again tomorrow because he despawned on us to soon tonight.<BR>
<BR>
I've also been told that the necter is the easier of the 3 quest items to get.<BR>
<BR>
So yeah, the quest sash rocks, is 41% haste and kicks ALL other haste items (aside from VP &quot;maybe&quot;) out of the game. What do you expect though, monks rock! (quote from Abashi, but if you haven't read monk community message boards you won't get it hehe)<BR>
<BR>
Good luck in your quests!<BR>
